href="erct-001T.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001T">Propositional maps</fr:link> are <fr:link
href="erct-003K.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-003K">embeddings</fr:link></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:meta
name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0049.agda"
type="external">erct-0049.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Any <fr:link
href="erct-001T.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001T">propositional map</fr:link> <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> is an <fr:link
href="erct-003K.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-003K">embedding</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1214</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>18</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>erct-0049</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Fixing <fr:tex>x,y:A</fr:tex> we must show that <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x = y  \to  fx=fy</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="erct-000W.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000W">invertible</fr:link>. By <fr:ref
addr="erct-002C"
href="erct-002C.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref> and <fr:ref
addr="erct-002D"
href="erct-002D.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>, it suffices to exhibit a <fr:link
href="erct-000U.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000U">biinverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f }</fr:tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">section</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">retraction</fr:link> need not be identical).</fr:p>

 <fr:p>We first define the <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">sections</fr:link> <fr:tex>s_{x,y} \colon  fx = fy  \to  x = y</fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> is assumed to be <fr:link
href="erct-001T.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001T">propositional</fr:link>, we have by <fr:ref
addr="erct-001R"
href="erct-001R.xml"
taxon="Example"></fr:ref> an assignment <fr:tex>\phi _{x,y}:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {} \cong _{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} } \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>. We therefore define <fr:tex>s_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .1</fr:tex>; the witness of <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">sectionhood</fr:link> can be constructed using <fr:tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \phi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} .2</fr:tex> modulo some identification algebra.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>To construct the <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-000Y">retractions</fr:link> <fr:tex>r_{x,y} \colon  fx=fy \to  x = y</fr:tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <fr:tex>\psi _{x,y}: \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( h:fx=fy \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathopen {} \left ( x, \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =_{ \mathsf {fiber} \, f \, \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} }  \mathopen {} \left ( y,h ^{-1} \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>, and we define <fr:tex>r_{x,y}h : \equiv   \mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {}</fr:tex>. It remains to show that for all <fr:tex>x,y:A</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>h \colon  x =y</fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,y}h \right ) \mathclose {} =h</fr:tex>. By induction on <fr:tex>h</fr:tex> it suffices to show that for all <fr:tex>x:A</fr:tex> we have <fr:tex>\mathsf {act}_{ -.1 } \mathopen {} \left ( \psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl} \right ) \mathclose {}  =  \mathsf {refl}</fr:tex>. We will deduce that <fr:tex>\psi _{x,x} \mathsf {refl}  =  \mathsf {refl}</fr:tex> from our assumption that <fr:tex>f \colon  A \to  B</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="erct-001T.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001T">propositional</fr:link> and thus <fr:link
href="erct-001T.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001T">fibred in sets</fr:link> via <fr:ref
addr="erct-001L"
href="erct-001L.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
